				 Retirement 
																								New Delhi, Nov. 28 (PTI): The Central Administrative Tribunal (CAT) has held that the government has no discretion in accepting or rejecting a voluntary retirement application in the absence of clear guidelines.																								We are satisfied that such a discretion and procedure can have relevance only in case where government is expressly given the right and discretion to accept the request for voluntary retirement, a tribunal bench said.																								The tribunal, hearing a petition a Delhi government employee had filed against the rejection of his early-retirement application, said the governments decision on such requests was without any legal basis as long as such a prescription (rule) is not there. 
